  <body>
    <p>A 37-year-old female patient has had asymptomatic lesions in the oral cavity and on the
lips since the age of 15. She had a history of thyroidectomy associated with the use of
radioiodine for the treatment of follicular thyroid carcinoma, and follicular adenoma
associated with Hashimoto&#x2019;s thyroiditis at age 23 years. Physical examination revealed
normochromic, flat papules in the paranasal and perioral regions and on the lips, as
well as hyperkeratotic papules on the dorsum of the hands (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="f01">Figures 1</xref> and <xref ref-type="fig" rid="f02">2</xref>). In the oral
cavity, we noticed the presence of multiple, normochromic papules on the jugal mucosa,
floor of the mouth and tongue (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="f01">Figure 1</xref>). Biopsies
of three lesions were performed: on the dorsum of the hand, compatible with benign acral
keratosis; on the lip, forming a fibroepithelial polyp; and on the oral mucosa, with
oral fibroma. High digestive endoscopy revealed duodenal hyperplastic polyps.
Mammography was unchanged.</p>
